17/*! \file dns/types.h
18 * \brief
19 * Including this file gives you type declarations suitable for use in
20 * .h files, which lets us avoid circular type reference problems.
21 * \brief
22 * To actually use a type or get declarations of its methods, you must
23 * include the appropriate .h file too.
24 */

227/*%
228 * rcodes.
229 */
230enum {
231 /*
232 * Standard rcodes.
233 */
234 dns_rcode_noerror = 0,
235#define dns_rcode_noerror ((dns_rcode_t)dns_rcode_noerror)
236 dns_rcode_formerr = 1,
237#define dns_rcode_formerr ((dns_rcode_t)dns_rcode_formerr)
238 dns_rcode_servfail = 2,
239#define dns_rcode_servfail ((dns_rcode_t)dns_rcode_servfail)
240 dns_rcode_nxdomain = 3,
241#define dns_rcode_nxdomain ((dns_rcode_t)dns_rcode_nxdomain)
242 dns_rcode_notimp = 4,
243#define dns_rcode_notimp ((dns_rcode_t)dns_rcode_notimp)
244 dns_rcode_refused = 5,
245#define dns_rcode_refused ((dns_rcode_t)dns_rcode_refused)
246 dns_rcode_yxdomain = 6,
247#define dns_rcode_yxdomain ((dns_rcode_t)dns_rcode_yxdomain)
248 dns_rcode_yxrrset = 7,
249#define dns_rcode_yxrrset ((dns_rcode_t)dns_rcode_yxrrset)
250 dns_rcode_nxrrset = 8,
251#define dns_rcode_nxrrset ((dns_rcode_t)dns_rcode_nxrrset)
252 dns_rcode_notauth = 9,
253#define dns_rcode_notauth ((dns_rcode_t)dns_rcode_notauth)
254 dns_rcode_notzone = 10,
255#define dns_rcode_notzone ((dns_rcode_t)dns_rcode_notzone)
256 /*
257 * Extended rcodes.
258 */
259 dns_rcode_badvers = 16,
260#define dns_rcode_badvers ((dns_rcode_t)dns_rcode_badvers)
261 dns_rcode_badcookie = 23
262#define dns_rcode_badcookie ((dns_rcode_t)dns_rcode_badcookie)
263 /*
264 * Update dns_rcodestats_create() and dns_rcodestats_increment()
265 * and this comment if a rcode > dns_rcode_badcookie is assigned.
266 */
267 /* Private space [3841..4095] */
268};

299/*%
300 * Trust levels. Must be kept in sync with trustnames[] in masterdump.c.
301 */
302enum {
303 /* Sentinel value; no data should have this trust level. */
304 dns_trust_none = 0,
305#define dns_trust_none ((dns_trust_t)dns_trust_none)
306
307 /*%
308 * Subject to DNSSEC validation but has not yet been validated
309 * dns_trust_pending_additional (from the additional section).
310 */
311 dns_trust_pending_additional = 1,
312#define dns_trust_pending_additional \
313 ((dns_trust_t)dns_trust_pending_additional)
314
315 dns_trust_pending_answer = 2,
316#define dns_trust_pending_answer ((dns_trust_t)dns_trust_pending_answer)
317
318 /*% Received in the additional section of a response. */
319 dns_trust_additional = 3,
320#define dns_trust_additional ((dns_trust_t)dns_trust_additional)
321
322 /* Received in a referral response. */
323 dns_trust_glue = 4,
324#define dns_trust_glue ((dns_trust_t)dns_trust_glue)
325
326 /* Answer from a non-authoritative server */
327 dns_trust_answer = 5,
328#define dns_trust_answer ((dns_trust_t)dns_trust_answer)
329
330 /* Received in the authority section as part of an
331 authoritative response */
332 dns_trust_authauthority = 6,
333#define dns_trust_authauthority ((dns_trust_t)dns_trust_authauthority)
334
335 /* Answer from an authoritative server */
336 dns_trust_authanswer = 7,
337#define dns_trust_authanswer ((dns_trust_t)dns_trust_authanswer)
338
339 /* Successfully DNSSEC validated */
340 dns_trust_secure = 8,
341#define dns_trust_secure ((dns_trust_t)dns_trust_secure)
342
343 /* This server is authoritative */
344 dns_trust_ultimate = 9
345#define dns_trust_ultimate ((dns_trust_t)dns_trust_ultimate)
346};
347
348#define DNS_TRUST_PENDING(x) ((x) == dns_trust_pending_answer || \
349 (x) == dns_trust_pending_additional)
350#define DNS_TRUST_ADDITIONAL(x) ((x) == dns_trust_additional || \
351 (x) == dns_trust_pending_additional)
352#define DNS_TRUST_GLUE(x) ((x) == dns_trust_glue)
353#define DNS_TRUST_ANSWER(x) ((x) == dns_trust_answer)

356/*%
357 * Name checking severities.
358 */
359typedef enum {
360 dns_severity_ignore,
361 dns_severity_warn,
362 dns_severity_fail
363} dns_severity_t;
364
365/*%
366 * DNS Serial Number Update Method.
367 *
368 * \li _none: Keep the current serial.
369 * \li _increment: Add one to the current serial, skipping 0.
370 * \li _unixtime: Set to the seconds since 00:00 Jan 1, 1970,
371 * if possible.
372 * \li _date: Set to today's date in YYYYMMDDVV format:
373 * (Year, Month, Day, Version)
374 */
375typedef enum {
376 dns_updatemethod_none = 0,
377 dns_updatemethod_increment,
378 dns_updatemethod_unixtime,
379 dns_updatemethod_date
380} dns_updatemethod_t;
381
382typedef enum {
383 dns_stale_answer_no,
384 dns_stale_answer_yes,
385 dns_stale_answer_conf
386} dns_stale_answer_t;
